body:
@v-lukanin It looks like it's at the `web3` level - there's a recent comment on this subject by `web3`'s maintainer [here](https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/434#issuecomment-321526814) and they are working on a solution for `web3 1.0`. 

The underlying issue seems to be about decoding.

Please let us know if you feel that Truffle should do something for this case, and leaving this issue open for a bit in case there are possible solutions.
